NDI Desktop Streamer — Installation
=====================================

The app ships with NDI and GStreamer NDI plugin bundled in lib/:

    lib/libndi.so.6.3.1   — NDI runtime (+ symlinks libndi.so.6, libndi.so)
    lib/libgstndi.so      — GStreamer NDI plugin

No system-wide NDI or GStreamer NDI install is needed.
Always launch via run.sh, which sets GST_PLUGIN_PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH
to point at lib/ before starting Python.


1. System packages (Ubuntu/Debian)
------------------------------------
sudo apt install \
    python3-gi \
    python3-gi-cairo \
    gir1.2-gtk-3.0 \
    python3-gst-1.0 \
    gstreamer1.0-plugins-base \
    gstreamer1.0-plugins-good \
    gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad \
    gstreamer1.0-x \
    libgstreamer1.0-0

# Wayland only (not needed for X11):
sudo apt install \
    gstreamer1.0-pipewire \
    pipewire \
    wireplumber \
    xdg-desktop-portal \
    xdg-desktop-portal-gtk   # or -gnome / -kde / -wlr depending on desktop


2. Python packages
------------------
sudo apt install python3-pillow python3-numpy


3. Run
------
./run.sh
./run.sh --name "My Custom Source Name"

The NDI source appears on the network as "Desktop Streamer" (or your chosen
name).  Connect from OBS, vMix, Zoom, etc.

Tray icons:
  Left icon  — tally light:  dark gray=standby  dark green=preview  bright red=on-air
  Right icon — mic status:   green=live          gray+slash=muted
  Left-click either icon → toggle mic mute


4. Firewall (ufw)
------------------
If ufw is active, open the ports NDI needs on the sending PC:

    # mDNS discovery — may already be open if avahi-daemon is installed,
    # but ufw can still block it if default policy is deny
    sudo ufw allow 5353/udp comment 'NDI mDNS discovery'

    # NDI video/audio data (covers up to ~10 simultaneous sources)
    sudo ufw allow 5959:5969/tcp comment 'NDI stream data'
    sudo ufw allow 5959:5969/udp comment 'NDI stream data'

    # Additional ranges — only needed for more than ~10 concurrent NDI sources
    sudo ufw allow 6960:6970/tcp comment 'NDI stream data (extra sources)'
    sudo ufw allow 6960:6970/udp comment 'NDI stream data (extra sources)'
    sudo ufw allow 7960:7970/tcp comment 'NDI stream data (extra sources)'
    sudo ufw allow 7960:7970/udp comment 'NDI stream data (extra sources)'

    # NDI Discovery Server — only if running a dedicated discovery server
    sudo ufw allow 5960/tcp comment 'NDI Discovery Server'

The receiving PC typically only needs outbound connections, which ufw allows
by default.  mDNS (5353/udp) should be open on both ends for source discovery.


5. Rebuilding lib/ from source
--------------------------------
See BUILD for step-by-step instructions to recompile libgstndi.so from
gst-plugins-rs and re-copy libndi.so from the NDI SDK.


6. Wayland
----------
On Wayland the app requests screen-capture permission via the XDG ScreenCast
portal on first launch (a screen-picker dialog appears).  Make sure the
portal is running:
    systemctl --user status xdg-desktop-portal
